---
import RoomLayout from '../../../layouts/RoomLayout.astro';
import BookBanner from '../../../components/BookBanner.astro';
import { getServerSupabase } from '../../../lib/supabase';
import { ffgVersions } from '../../../data/ffgVersions';

export const prerender = false;

let reviewCount = 0;
try {
  const supabase = getServerSupabase(Astro);
  const { data: work } = await supabase
    .from('works')
    .select('id')
    .eq('slug', 'schools-of-the-republic')
    .maybeSingle();
  if (work?.id) {
    const { count } = await supabase
      .from('reviews')
      .select('id', { count: 'exact', head: true })
      .eq('work_id', work.id)
      .eq('is_published', true);
    if (typeof count === 'number') reviewCount = count;
  }
} catch {
  /* swallow */
}

const VERSIONS = ffgVersions;
---
<RoomLayout
  room="writing"
  title="The Forgotten Forever Gift to Public Schools"
  subtitle="The Story of the Land America Set Aside for Its Schools - and What Became of It. Volume I of A Forever Gift (Looking Back), by Margaret Bird and David Sullivan. Current reading draft, June 2026."
  width="prose"
  sourceId="writing-schools-of-the-republic"
>
  <BookBanner slot="before-title" direction="back" />

  <article class="prose prose-slate max-w-none prose-a:text-blue-700 prose-a:underline">
    <span class="eyebrow">Volume I · Bird and Sullivan · A Forever Gift, Book One</span>

    <section class="version-bar" aria-label="Draft versions">
      <p class="vb-intro"><strong>Draft versions.</strong> This book is being written in the open. Each button below is a saved draft — <strong>click one</strong> to see what changed in it and download that draft. Newest first.</p>
      <div class="vb-row" id="vbRow" role="group">
        {VERSIONS.map((d, i) => (
          <button type="button" class="vb-btn" data-i={i} aria-current={i === 0 ? 'true' : 'false'}>
            {d.v}{i === 0 ? ' · current' : ''}
          </button>
        ))}
      </div>
      <p class="vb-note" id="vbNote"><span class="vb-date">{VERSIONS[0].v + " · " + VERSIONS[0].date}</span>{" — " + VERSIONS[0].note + " "}<a class="vb-dl" href={VERSIONS[0].file}>Download this version (Word) →</a></p>
      <script type="application/json" id="vbData" set:html={JSON.stringify(VERSIONS)} />
    </section>
    <script is:inline>
      (function(){var el=document.getElementById("vbData");if(!el)return;var data=JSON.parse(el.textContent);
      var note=document.getElementById("vbNote");var btns=document.querySelectorAll("#vbRow .vb-btn");
      function sel(i){for(var j=0;j<btns.length;j++)btns[j].setAttribute("aria-current",j===i?"true":"false");
      var d=data[i];note.innerHTML='<span class="vb-date">'+d.v+' · '+d.date+'</span> — '+d.note+' <a class="vb-dl" href="'+d.file+'">Download this version (Word) →</a>';}
      for(var j=0;j<btns.length;j++)(function(k){btns[k].addEventListener("click",function(){sel(k);});})(j);})();
    </script>


    <p>
      <em>The Forgotten Forever Gift to Public Schools</em> is Volume 1 of the Looking Back /
      Looking Forward two-volume work — the synthesizing analytic treatment of
      America's longest-running fiduciary experiment — the school-land trusts
      created beginning with the 1785 Land Ordinance and extended through every
      state admission from Ohio to Hawaii. The book traces how the trusts were
      designed, how they have drifted, and what design principles their
      successor structures will need.
    </p>

    <p>
      The per-state evidentiary record this synthesis draws on lives in
      America's School Trust Library — in its
      <a href="/atlas/">Atlas</a>, its <a href="/maps/">Map Room</a>, and
      its <a href="/counting/">Counting House</a>, where it remains alive and
      continues to be added to. The book draws on that record without
      duplicating it.
    </p>

    <h2>The shape of the book (current June 2026)</h2>
    <p>
      The current reading draft opens with the inheritance itself, then turns
      through the duties that make a school-land grant a real trust: loyalty,
      prudence, competence, accounting, supervision, enforcement, and public
      visibility. The latest full text is the v30 Word draft:
      <a href="/drafts/schools-of-the-republic-latest.docx">download the current draft (Word)</a>.
    </p>
    <p><strong>Part One - The Gift and the Duty</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Chapter 1 - The Inheritance Still Standing</li>
      <li>Chapter 2 - The World That Made the Gift</li>
      <li>Chapter 3 - The Punctilio of Honor</li>
      <li>Chapter 4 - Loyalty: The Gift Treated as Pocket Money</li>
      <li>Chapter 5 - Prudence: Do Not Eat the Seed Corn</li>
      <li>Chapter 6 - Competence and Accounting: The Books Must Tell the Truth</li>
      <li>Chapter 7 - Supervision and Enforcement: Someone Has to Watch the Watcher</li>
      <li>Chapter 8 - The Money Must Be Seen</li>
      <li>Chapter 9 - What Citizens Can Do Now</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Part Two - The Granted States, A to Z</strong></p>
    <p>
      Thirty-three state portraits, from Alabama through Wyoming, show how the
      same public-school inheritance was kept, spent, defended, neglected, or
      rebuilt in different states. The appendix then accounts for the
      non-grant states.
    </p>
    <p class="migration-note">
      <em>This URL is retained for link stability from the book's earlier
      working title, Schools of the Republic. The current title and
      downloadable draft are the ones shown here.</em>
    </p>

    <h2>The per-state record lives in the Library</h2>
    <p>
      The per-state dossiers — constitutional architecture, admission-act
      provisions, permanent fund corpus, federal grant acreage, and current
      trust-integrity status — live in the Library's
      <a href="/atlas/">Atlas</a>, with state cohort pages organized by era
      under <a href="/atlas/">/atlas/</a>. The same record surfaces in the
      <a href="/maps/">Map Room</a> for transparency posture and the
      <a href="/counting/">Counting House</a> for fund balances and audit
      disclosure. Each state's dossier also has a Reading Room entry at
      <code>/reading/us-XX/</code>.
    </p>

    <hr class="archival-divider">

    <p>This volume is the synthesis. The <a href="/atlas/">Atlas</a>, the <a href="/counting/">Counting House</a>, and the companion volume <a href="/writing/stewards-of-the-republic/">Stewards of the Republic</a> draw on the same evidentiary substrate.</p>

    <section class="comment-box" aria-label="Leave a comment" id="commentBox">
      <h2 class="cb-h">Found something? Tell us.</h2>
      <p class="cb-intro">Anyone can comment — no account needed. Type a note, record your voice, add a photo or video, or attach a file. It goes straight to the authors.</p>
      <textarea id="cbText" class="cb-text" rows="4" placeholder="Your comment…"></textarea>
      <div class="cb-row">
        <input id="cbName" class="cb-in" type="text" placeholder="Name (optional)" />
        <input id="cbEmail" class="cb-in" type="email" placeholder="Email (optional — for a reply)" />
      </div>
      <div class="cb-tools">
        <button type="button" id="cbRec" class="cb-tool">🎤 Record audio</button>
        <label class="cb-tool">📷 Photo / video<input id="cbCam" type="file" accept="image/*,video/*" capture multiple hidden /></label>
        <label class="cb-tool">📎 Attach file<input id="cbFile" type="file" multiple hidden /></label>
      </div>
      <ul id="cbList" class="cb-list"></ul>
      <button type="button" id="cbSend" class="cb-send">Send comment</button>
      <p id="cbMsg" class="cb-msg" role="status"></p>
    </section>
    <script is:inline>
      (function(){
        var items=[];var listEl=document.getElementById('cbList');var msg=document.getElementById('cbMsg');
        function render(){listEl.innerHTML=items.map(function(it,i){return '<li>'+it.label+' <button type="button" data-i="'+i+'" class="cb-rm">remove</button></li>';}).join('');}
        listEl&&listEl.addEventListener('click',function(e){var t=e.target;if(t&&t.classList&&t.classList.contains('cb-rm')){items.splice(+t.getAttribute('data-i'),1);render();}});
        function addFiles(fl){for(var i=0;i<fl.length;i++){items.push({file:fl[i],label:(fl[i].name||'file')+' ('+Math.round(fl[i].size/1024)+' KB)'});}render();}
        var cam=document.getElementById('cbCam'),file=document.getElementById('cbFile');
        cam&&cam.addEventListener('change',function(){addFiles(cam.files);cam.value='';});
        file&&file.addEventListener('change',function(){addFiles(file.files);file.value='';});
        var rec=document.getElementById('cbRec'),mr=null,chunks=[];
        rec&&rec.addEventListener('click',function(){
          if(mr&&mr.state==='recording'){mr.stop();return;}
          if(!navigator.mediaDevices||!window.MediaRecorder){msg.style.color='#b91c1c';msg.textContent='Audio recording is not supported here — you can still attach a file.';return;}
          navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia({audio:true}).then(function(stream){
            chunks=[];mr=new MediaRecorder(stream);
            mr.ondataavailable=function(e){if(e.data&&e.data.size)chunks.push(e.data);};
            mr.onstop=function(){var blob=new Blob(chunks,{type:(chunks[0]&&chunks[0].type)||'audio/webm'});var ext=(blob.type.indexOf('ogg')>-1?'ogg':'webm');var f=new File([blob],'voice-'+Date.now()+'.'+ext,{type:blob.type});items.push({file:f,label:'🎤 Voice note ('+Math.round(f.size/1024)+' KB)'});render();stream.getTracks().forEach(function(t){t.stop();});rec.textContent='🎤 Record audio';rec.classList.remove('cb-recording');};
            mr.start();rec.textContent='⏹ Stop recording';rec.classList.add('cb-recording');
          }).catch(function(){msg.style.color='#b91c1c';msg.textContent='Could not access the microphone.';});
        });
        var send=document.getElementById('cbSend');
        send&&send.addEventListener('click',function(){
          var text=(document.getElementById('cbText').value||'').trim();
          if(!text&&items.length===0){msg.style.color='#b91c1c';msg.textContent='Please write a comment or add a recording or file.';return;}
          send.disabled=true;msg.style.color='#475569';msg.textContent='Sending…';
          var fd=new FormData();fd.append('text',text);fd.append('name',document.getElementById('cbName').value||'');fd.append('email',document.getElementById('cbEmail').value||'');fd.append('page_url',location.href);
          items.forEach(function(it){fd.append('files',it.file,it.file.name);});
          fetch('/api/comment',{method:'POST',body:fd}).then(function(r){return r.json().then(function(j){return {ok:r.ok,j:j};});}).then(function(res){
            if(res.ok&&res.j&&res.j.ok){msg.style.color='#166534';msg.textContent='Thank you — your comment was sent to the authors.';document.getElementById('cbText').value='';items=[];render();send.disabled=false;}
            else{msg.style.color='#b91c1c';msg.textContent=(res.j&&res.j.error)||'Sorry, something went wrong. Please try again.';send.disabled=false;}
          }).catch(function(){msg.style.color='#b91c1c';msg.textContent='Sorry, something went wrong. Please try again.';send.disabled=false;});
        });
      })();
    </script>

    <p class="reviews-link">
      <a href="/reading/schools-of-the-republic/reviews/">Reviews ({reviewCount})</a>
    </p>
  </article>

  <style>
    .version-bar{margin:1.25rem 0 1.75rem;padding:1rem 1.1rem;border:1px solid var(--rule-border,#e5e7eb);border-radius:6px;background:var(--linen-card,#fafaf7);}
    .vb-intro{font-family:var(--font-sans);font-size:.9rem;color:#334155;margin:0 0 .85rem;line-height:1.5;}
    .vb-row{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:.5rem;margin-bottom:.85rem;}
    .version-bar .vb-btn{font-family:var(--font-sans);font-size:.9rem;font-weight:600;padding:.45rem .9rem;border:1.5px solid var(--deep-navy,#1e3a5f);border-radius:6px;background:#fff;color:var(--deep-navy,#1e3a5f);cursor:pointer;box-shadow:0 1px 2px rgba(15,23,42,.08);}
    .version-bar .vb-btn:hover{background:#eef2f7;}
    .version-bar .vb-btn[aria-current="true"]{background:var(--deep-navy,#1e3a5f);color:#fff;box-shadow:0 2px 5px rgba(15,23,42,.18);}
    .vb-note{font-family:var(--font-sans);font-size:.9rem;color:#334155;margin:0;line-height:1.55;}
    .vb-note .vb-date{font-weight:700;color:var(--deep-navy,#1e3a5f);}
    .vb-dl{color:#1d4ed8;text-decoration:underline;font-weight:600;white-space:nowrap;}
    .comment-box{margin:2rem 0 1rem;padding:1.25rem 1.25rem 1.4rem;border:1px solid var(--rule-border,#e5e7eb);border-left:3px solid var(--old-gold,#8b7355);border-radius:6px;background:var(--linen-card,#fafaf7);}
    .cb-h{font-family:var(--font-serif,Georgia,serif);font-size:1.25rem;color:var(--deep-navy,#1e3a5f);margin:0 0 .4rem;}
    .cb-intro{font-family:var(--font-sans);font-size:.9rem;color:#475569;margin:0 0 .9rem;line-height:1.5;}
    .cb-text{width:100%;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:var(--font-sans);font-size:.95rem;padding:.6rem .7rem;border:1px solid #cbd5e1;border-radius:6px;resize:vertical;}
    .cb-row{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:.6rem;margin:.6rem 0;}
    .cb-in{flex:1 1 200px;font-family:var(--font-sans);font-size:.9rem;padding:.5rem .6rem;border:1px solid #cbd5e1;border-radius:6px;}
    .cb-tools{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:.5rem;margin:.4rem 0 .2rem;}
    .cb-tool{font-family:var(--font-sans);font-size:.88rem;font-weight:600;padding:.45rem .8rem;border:1.5px solid var(--deep-navy,#1e3a5f);border-radius:6px;background:#fff;color:var(--deep-navy,#1e3a5f);cursor:pointer;display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:.3rem;}
    .cb-tool:hover{background:#eef2f7;}
    .cb-recording{background:#b91c1c !important;color:#fff !important;border-color:#b91c1c !important;}
    .cb-list{list-style:none;padding:0;margin:.6rem 0;font-family:var(--font-sans);font-size:.85rem;color:#334155;}
    .cb-list li{padding:.25rem 0;}
    .cb-rm{margin-left:.4rem;font-size:.78rem;color:#b91c1c;background:none;border:none;cursor:pointer;text-decoration:underline;}
    .cb-send{margin-top:.6rem;font-family:var(--font-sans);font-size:.95rem;font-weight:700;padding:.55rem 1.2rem;border:none;border-radius:6px;background:var(--deep-navy,#1e3a5f);color:#fff;cursor:pointer;}
    .cb-send:disabled{opacity:.6;cursor:default;}
    .cb-msg{font-family:var(--font-sans);font-size:.88rem;margin:.6rem 0 0;min-height:1.1em;}
    .reviews-link {
      font-family: var(--font-sans);
      font-size: 0.88rem;
      margin-top: 1.5rem;
      color: #475569;
    }
  </style>
</RoomLayout>
